article.headline: Arkansas State 91, Liberty 64
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- J.J. Montgomery scored 21 points to lead Arkansas State to a 91-65 victory Saturday over Liberty. Five players for ASU (2-1) scored in double digits as the Indians easily outdistanced the visitors. Liberty (0-2) trailed 46-30 at the half. David Dees led Liberty's scoring with 15 points, while Larry Blair added 11. Two of ASU's double-digit scorers came off the bench to get their points, with Marcus Ardison getting 13 points in 16 minutes of play and Jerry Nichols 10 points. Starters Dewarick Spencer and Isaac Wells added 12 points each.
